AngloGold Ashanti Limited (AU) Getting Somewhat Favorable News Coverage, Study Finds

Cirilo Laguardia |
Sábado, Julio 15, 2017







Their 52-Week High and Low are noted here. The firm earned "Buy" rating on Monday, January 18 by Goldman Sachs. The rating was upgraded by Goldman Sachs to "Buy" on Friday, January 15. (The) cut shares of AngloGold Ashanti Limited from a "buy" rating to a "neutral" rating in a research note on Monday, April 24th.AngloGold Ashanti Limited (AU) traded up 0.765% during midday trading on Friday, hitting $9.875. Citigroup downgraded the shares of AU in report on Tuesday, May 10 to "Sell" rating. Two analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, seven have issued a hold rating and three have assigned a buy rating to the company's stock. Therefore 100% are positive. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $11.16 and a 200 day moving average of $11.41. It has underperformed by 35.59% the S&P500.The move comes after 7 months negative chart setup for the $4.02B company.
Taking a glance at where the stock might be directed in the future, on a consensus basis, the sell-side has a 52 week price target of $12.79 on the stock, this valuation is based on 3 number of opinions. Jefferies maintained BioScrip Inc (NASDAQ:BIOS) on Thursday, June 8 with "Buy" rating. The rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets with "Outperform" on Wednesday, November 4. Barclays Capital downgraded the shares of MOS in report on Tuesday, April 19 to "Underweight" rating. The firm earned "Buy" rating on Tuesday, August 11 by SunTrust.Shares of Anglogold Ashanti Ltd (NYSE:AU) now have an Average Brokerage Recommendation of 2.2, number of Recs in ABR is 5 while industry rank of the company by ABR is 176 out of 265. The Company's business activities span the spectrum of the mining value chain. It has a 65.72 P/E ratio. The Company's main product is gold. Its last month's stock price volatility remained 2.78% which for the week approaches 2.96%.ValuEngine cut shares of AngloGold Ashanti Limited (NYSE:AU) from a hold rating to a sell rating in a research note published on Tuesday, June 27th.The Mosaic Company is a producer and marketer of concentrated phosphate and potash crop nutrients. The Firm operates through Infusion Services segment. The Firm is a supplier of phosphate- and potash crop nutrients and animal feed ingredients. The analysts estimated EPS for the higher end at 0.24 and lower end at 0.18 while the year ago reported earnings per share was 1.51. The company's 5 year Earnings per share growth and Capital Spending growth remains at -47.39 and -14.62. Total debt to equity ratio of the company for most recent quarter is 0.8 whereas long term debt to equity ratio for most recent quarter is 0.79.Investors sentiment decreased to 0.8 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.57, from 1.46 in 2016Q3. 16 funds opened positions while 26 raised stakes. Its down 1.46% from 23.37 million shares previously. Creative Planning reported 2,700 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Jpmorgan Chase And has 0% invested in BioScrip Inc (NASDAQ:BIOS) for 186,407 shares. Nationwide Fund Advisors holds 0% or 77,922 shares. Kempner Capital Mngmt reported 2.73% in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS). Deerfield Mgmt Co has 1.97M shares. Tower Cap Limited Liability (Trc) reported 4,449 shares. Pittenger And Anderson invested in 0% or 50 shares. Thompson Siegel & Walmsley Ltd Liability Corporation has 0% invested in BioScrip Inc (NASDAQ:BIOS). The insider Johnson Denise C bought 803 shares worth $18,933.The company surged 1.42% and closed its last trading session at $9.88. About 814,606 shares traded. It has underperformed by 24.57% the S&P500.




